        # Meeting with Jost Muth and Lena Julie Freund from the Fraunhofer IME Aachen (28.04.21)

        In order to analyze our samples far more in detail, Sebastian Palluk suggested us to talk to the capillary electrophoresis (CE) experts from the Fraunhofer IME in Aachen.
        At the IME they use an ABI3730 Genetic Analyzer to measure the length of for example PCR products. For this analysis method, our DNA has to be labelled with a fluorescent dye.
        Mrs Freund suggested us the 6FAM dye because of its low costs and good results.
        Through multiple questions, we concluded that the CE is an optimal analyzing method for our samples because the DNA hasn't to be double-stranded owing to the fact that the samples are denatured beforehand. Furthermore, the size range from 35 bp to 500 bp within 1 bp resolution is the range of our synthesized fragments.
        After the questions, Mrs Freund and Mr Muth offered us to support our project by trying to analyze our samples, help us with the interpretation of the data and being open to questions in the future.
        Later, we had some more meetings to work out the analysis of our created DNA samples, which subsequently performed well. 
        Our Modeling team used this data to adapt and improve their model. 
        

