        # Meeting with Maximilian Schmidt from FZ Jülich
        
        Maximilian Schmidt is member of the section IBG-4 Bioinformatics in FZ Jülich.
        We contacted him referring to some questions about the Nanopore Sequencing with the MinION from Oxford Nanopore. 
        For our progress in the lab, it is necessary to sequence the DNA strands we created, but there are some difficulties because of our specific method. 
        So, we scheduled some meetings with Maximilian where we presented our project and talked about possible methods of sequencing.
        He offered to come to us in the lab and bring his MinION so that we can analyze our samples with his help.
        It was very interesting to learn about the sequence method of the MinION and it was a great opportunity to ask as many questions about it as we want. 
        Maximilian was very committed sharing his experiences with us and was very helpful.
        At the end of the day, sequencing was successful and we had a lot of new data for our project progress. 
